class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 21, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xmq1665702675709.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xmq1665702675709.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xmq1665702675709.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xmq1665702675709\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                           \n Device Type\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Name of the device translation table to use for this print job model.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xmq1665702675709__p_d9659e1_d9660e1_d9661e1\">The device table specified must be compatible with the physical printing device to be used.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xmq1665702675709__p_d9662e1_d9663e1_d9664e1\">By convention print job model names start with <code class=\"ph codeph\">P_</code>. Print job models named <code class=\"ph codeph\">P_<var class=\"keyword varname\">XXX</var>X</code> (such as <code class=\"ph codeph\">P_MSWINX</code>) use enhanced printing features.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"xmq1665702675709__table_d1016e1_d1017e1_d1018e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Commonly Used Device Translation Tables</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xmq1665702675709__table_d1016e1_d1017e1_d1018e1__entry__1\">\n Device Translation Table\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xmq1665702675709__table_d1016e1_d1017e1_d1018e1__entry__2\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xmq1665702675709__table_d1016e1_d1017e1_d1018e1__entry__1\">\n P_MSWINX\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xmq1665702675709__table_d1016e1_d1017e1_d1018e1__entry__2\">\n Uses the Microsoft print API to print through the print manager. Prints widgets with proportional fonts and with representation instead of value; respects widget properties.\n <p class=\"p\">If selected, <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print Queue</span> must be set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">PRINTMAN</code>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xmq1665702675709__table_d1016e1_d1017e1_d1018e1__entry__1\">\n P_MSWIN3\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xmq1665702675709__table_d1016e1_d1017e1_d1018e1__entry__2\">\n Uses the Microsoft print API to print through print manager. Does not support widget printing.\n <p class=\"p\">If selected, <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print Queue</span> must be set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">PRINTMAN</code>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xmq1665702675709__table_d1016e1_d1017e1_d1018e1__entry__1\">\n P_DEFAULT\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xmq1665702675709__table_d1016e1_d1017e1_d1018e1__entry__2\">\n Sends ASCII-only characters to printer. Line feed and form feed are the only control characters sent to the printer.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xmq1665702675709__table_d1016e1_d1017e1_d1018e1__entry__1\">\n P_LASERJET2\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xmq1665702675709__table_d1016e1_d1017e1_d1018e1__entry__2\">\n Sends HP PCL control characters to printer.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xmq1665702675709__table_d1016e1_d1017e1_d1018e1__entry__1\">\n P_X11\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xmq1665702675709__table_d1016e1_d1017e1_d1018e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                        Sends extended Postscript commands to printer.\n                     </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xiz1665702989085.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Device Translation Tables for Printing</a><p>Printer device tables are a collection of sequences (control codes) associated with specific logical functions (such as bold, form feed, and init). The sequences begin with the escape character and are referred to as escape sequences.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533796\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533796\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Device Type Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Device Type Name of the device translation table to use for this print job model. The device table specified must be compatible with the physical printing device to be used. By convention print job model names start with P_ . Print job models named P_ XXX X (such as P_MSWINX ) use enhanced printing features. Table 1. Commonly Used Device Translation Tables Device Translation Table Description P_MSWINX Uses the Microsoft print API to print through the print manager. Prints widgets with proportional fonts and with representation instead of value; respects widget properties. If selected, Print Queue must be set to PRINTMAN . P_MSWIN3 Uses the Microsoft print API to print through print manager. Does not support widget printing. If selected, Print Queue must be set to PRINTMAN . P_DEFAULT Sends ASCII-only characters to printer. Line feed and form feed are the only control characters sent to the printer. P_LASERJET2 Sends HP PCL control characters to printer. P_X11 Sends extended Postscript commands to printer. Related Links Device Translation Tables for Printing Printer device tables are a collection of sequences (control codes) associated with specific logical functions (such as bold, form feed, and init). The sequences begin with the escape character and are referred to as escape sequences. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}